    {
      "id": "view-boundary",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "View Boundary (Multi-Dev Contract)",
      "position": {
        "x": 900,
        "y": 960
      },
      "width": 880,
      "height": 520,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "## View Boundary (Multi-Dev Contract)\n\nViews are the lowest-level graph-defined unit.\n\nEverything above views is graph-defined. Everything below views is code-defined.\n\n### Graph-Defined (above the line)\n- Dictionaries (nodeDefs, skills, views)\n- Node classes and schemas\n- View declarations (intent + payload)\n- Task graphs and workflows\n- Node instances and data\n\n### Code-Defined (below the line)\n- Rendering runtime and components\n- Event plumbing and UI wiring\n- Security/sanitization\n- Performance and caching\n\n### Reasoning\n- Views act as stable API surfaces across teams.\n- Graphs are declarative, reviewable, and portable.\n- Runtime stays centralized for correctness and policy.\n\nIf you’re unsure: if it changes what the view **is**, it’s graph-defined. If it changes how the view **renders**, it’s code-defined.",
        "_classBinding": {
          "key": "markdown",
          "sourceRef": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
          "ref": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
          "identity": {
            "graphId": "markdown_class",
            "name": "markdown Node Class",
            "version": "0.1.0",
            "description": "Canonical markdown content node.",
            "createdAt": "2026-02-24T20:05:15Z",
            "updatedAt": "2026-03-24T01:20:00.000Z"
          },
          "intent": "graph",
          "meaning": "Canonical markdown content node.",
          "description": "Canonical markdown content node.",
          "defaults": {},
          "nodeDef": {
            "key": "markdown",
            "ref": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
